main event: An observer reported seeing a round object the size of the moon, which was white and pink, making a buzzing sound as it flew in a straight line and then faded away after about three minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed for 15-20 minutes.,The object emitted a buzzing sound.,The sighting occurred on 8 March 1956.,The object was described as white and pink and about the size of the moon.,Conclusions indicated that it might have been a balloon or aircraft.
sighted object: a round object the size of the moon
